    "key": "pendingIdeas",
    "value": "[{\"id\":\"community-article-curator\",\"title\":\"Article Curator\",\"description\":\"A StumbleUpon-style article discovery app built entirely from a phone — surfaces interesting articles based on your interests with one-tap browsing.\\n\\nRecreation prompt: Build a StumbleUpon-style article curator as a static web app on adam-harris.alphaclaw.app:\\n1. Create a mobile-first web app at articles.adam-harris.alphaclaw.app with a 'Discover' button and reading view\\n2. Configure interest profile: AI/automation, agency operations, Next.js, Contentful, headless CMS, enterprise tech\\n3. Use Brave Search API to find articles matching Adam's interests, plus RSS feeds from key tech blogs\\n4. Use OpenAI GPT-4 to score relevance and generate 2-line summaries\\n5. Build the UI with Web Components: <cc-article-card>, <cc-discover-button>, <cc-reading-list>\\n6. Store reading history and preferences as JSON in the app's data directory\\n7. Daily cron job: curate top 5 articles and post digest to Slack\\n8. Deploy as a static web app — accessible from phone\\n\\nIntegrations used: Brave Search (discovery), OpenAI (scoring/summarizing), Slack (daily digest), static web app (UI).\",\"category\":\"Product\",\"status\":\"new\",\"feasibility\":9,\"impact\":7,\"effort\":\"Medium\",\"compositeScore\":7.6,\"tags\":[\"reading\",\"curation\",\"from-community\"],\"similarSolutions\":[],\"source\":\"community:article-curator\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-02-10\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-02-10\",\"completedAt\":null}]",
    "updatedAt": "2026-02-12T15:33:22.074Z"
  },
